    question:
      '<div class="content__u3I1 question-content__JfgR"><div><p>A <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Perfect_number" target="_blank"><strong>perfect number</strong></a> is a <strong>positive integer</strong> that is equal to the sum of its <strong>positive divisors</strong>, excluding the number itself. A <strong>divisor</strong> of an integer <code>x</code> is an integer that can divide <code>x</code> evenly.</p>\n<p>Given an integer <code>n</code>, return <code>true</code><em> if </em><code>n</code><em> is a perfect number, otherwise return </em><code>false</code>.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><strong>Example 1:</strong></p>\n<pre><strong>Input:</strong> num = 28\n<strong>Output:</strong> true\n<strong>Explanation:</strong> 28 = 1 + 2 + 4 + 7 + 14\n1, 2, 4, 7, and 14 are all divisors of 28.\n</pre>\n<p><strong>Example 2:</strong></p>\n<pre><strong>Input:</strong> num = 6\n<strong>Output:</strong> true\n</pre>\n<p><strong>Example 3:</strong></p>\n<pre><strong>Input:</strong> num = 496\n<strong>Output:</strong> true\n</pre>\n<p><strong>Example 4:</strong></p>\n<pre><strong>Input:</strong> num = 8128\n<strong>Output:</strong> true\n</pre>\n<p><strong>Example 5:</strong></p>\n<pre><strong>Input:</strong> num = 2\n<strong>Output:</strong> false\n</pre>\n<p> </p>\n<p><strong>Constraints:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><code>1 &lt;= num &lt;= 10<sup>8</sup></code></li>\n</ul>\n</div></div>',
