      '<div class="content__u3I1 question-content__JfgR"><div><p>Given an array <code>A</code> of integers, a <em>ramp</em> is a tuple <code>(i, j)</code> for which <code>i &lt; j</code> and <code>A[i] &lt;= A[j]</code>.  The width of such a ramp is <code>j - i</code>.</p>\n<p>Find the maximum width of a ramp in <code>A</code>.  If one doesn\'t exist, return 0.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><strong>Example 1:</strong></p>\n<pre><strong>Input: </strong><span id="example-input-1-1">[6,0,8,2,1,5]</span>\n<strong>Output: </strong><span id="example-output-1">4</span>\n<strong>Explanation: </strong>\nThe maximum width ramp is achieved at (i, j) = (1, 5): A[1] = 0 and A[5] = 5.\n</pre>\n<div>\n<p><strong>Example 2:</strong></p>\n<pre><strong>Input: </strong><span id="example-input-2-1">[9,8,1,0,1,9,4,0,4,1]</span>\n<strong>Output: </strong><span id="example-output-2">7</span>\n<strong>Explanation: </strong>\nThe maximum width ramp is achieved at (i, j) = (2, 9): A[2] = 1 and A[9] = 1.\n</pre>\n</div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong></p>\n<ol>\n<li><code>2 &lt;= A.length &lt;= 50000</code></li>\n<li><code>0 &lt;= A[i] &lt;= 50000</code></li>\n</ol>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div>\n<div> </div>\n</div>\n</div></div>',
