      '<div class="content__u3I1 question-content__JfgR"><div>Given an integer array <code>arr</code>, return <code>true</code> if there are three consecutive odd numbers in the array. Otherwise, return <code>false</code>.\n<p> </p>\n<p><strong>Example 1:</strong></p>\n<pre><strong>Input:</strong> arr = [2,6,4,1]\n<strong>Output:</strong> false\n<b>Explanation:</b> There are no three consecutive odds.\n</pre>\n<p><strong>Example 2:</strong></p>\n<pre><strong>Input:</strong> arr = [1,2,34,3,4,5,7,23,12]\n<strong>Output:</strong> true\n<b>Explanation:</b> [5,7,23] are three consecutive odds.\n</pre>\n<p> </p>\n<p><strong>Constraints:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><code>1 &lt;= arr.length &lt;= 1000</code></li>\n<li><code>1 &lt;= arr[i] &lt;= 1000</code></li>\n</ul>\n</div></div>',
